@startuml
title Incoming Update Processing

actor "Telegram Server" as Server
participant "Protocol Engine" as PE
participant "Update Dispatcher" as UD
participant "Sequence Tracker" as ST
participant "Data Model" as DM
participant "Histories Registry" as HR
participant "History" as H
participant "Change Notifier" as CN
participant "Session Controller" as SC
participant "Notification Center" as NC

== Startup: Fetch Initial State ==

UD -> PE : request initial update state
PE -> Server : get state
Server --> PE : current counters (pts, qts, seq, date)
PE --> UD : deliver initial state
UD -> ST : initialize global counters

== Server-Pushed Update Arrives ==

Server -> PE : push updates payload
PE -> UD : deliver updates payload

== Classify Payload ==

alt Short form (short message or short chat message)
    UD -> DM : check referenced users, chats, reply-to, forward, mention entities loaded
    alt Required entity not loaded
        UD -> UD : treat as not-loaded
        UD -> PE : schedule Difference Request (gap due to missing entity)
        PE -> Server : get difference (full range)
        Server --> PE : messages, chats, users, new state
        PE --> UD : deliver difference
        UD -> DM : apply messages, chats, users
        UD -> ST : reset counters to server-provided values
    else All entities loaded
        UD -> ST : consult global Sequence Tracker with pts/seq/count
    end
else Combined updates form
    UD -> ST : consult global Sequence Tracker for sequence ordering
end

== Sequence Tracker Decision ==

alt Update is next expected (no gap)
    ST --> UD : apply update
    UD -> ST : advance local counter
else Update is older or duplicate
    ST --> UD : skip update
    UD -> UD : discard update
else Gap detected
    ST --> UD : gap detected - buffer update and schedule Difference Request
    UD -> UD : buffer incoming update

    == Gap-Filling via Difference Request ==

    alt Global stream gap
        UD -> PE : request general difference (from-pts to server pts)
        PE -> Server : get difference
        Server --> PE : messages, chats, users, new state
        PE --> UD : deliver difference
        UD -> DM : apply difference messages and peer changes
        UD -> ST : reset global counters to server-provided values
    else Channel Entity gap
        UD -> PE : request channel difference (channel, from-pts)
        PE -> Server : get channel difference
        alt Normal channel difference
            Server --> PE : channel messages, chats, users, new pts
            PE --> UD : deliver channel difference
            UD -> DM : apply channel messages and peer changes
            UD -> ST : reset channel Sequence Tracker counters
        else Over-long channel difference
            Server --> PE : too long flag
            PE --> UD : over-long response
            UD -> DM : trigger full channel reload
        end
    end

    UD -> UD : apply buffered update(s)
end

== Apply Update to Data Model ==

UD -> DM : apply update (message, edit, deletion, read mark,\npeer change, typing action, etc.)
DM -> HR : locate or create History for target peer
HR -> H : process Message Item (new or edited)
H --> HR : message stored
HR --> DM : done

== Publish Change Events ==

DM -> CN : publish peer, history, and message change events

CN -> SC : history view refresh notification
SC -> H : refresh affected History display

CN -> NC : new message event
NC -> NC : apply mute and quiet-hours rules
NC -> NC : schedule notification via Notification Backend

== Edge Cases ==

group No-updates timeout
    UD -> PE : send keepalive ping to Telegram Server
    PE -> Server : ping
    Server --> PE : pong
end

group Force-logout service notification
    UD -> UD : detect force-logout notification kind
    UD -> SC : trigger logout
end

group New server session notification
    UD -> UD : detect new server session created
    UD -> ST : re-synchronize counters
    UD -> PE : schedule Difference Request to resync state
end

group Out-of-order combined updates
    UD -> UD : wait on sequence timer for missing predecessor
    alt Predecessor arrives in time
        UD -> UD : apply in correct sequence order
    else Timeout waiting for predecessor
        UD -> PE : schedule Difference Request
    end
end

@enduml
